# Local secrets directory — Firebase service-account JSON,
# any future API credentials, etc. Anything here is mounted into
# the container at runtime and must NEVER be committed.
# `*` + negated `.md` lets us ship docs (README explaining what
# files go here) while keeping the actual secrets out.
secrets/*
!secrets/*.md

# temp directories
.tmp
.temp

# Runtime data
pids
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo
